
[1]roundness

   ROUND'NESS, n.

   1. The quality of being round, circular, spherical, globular or
   cylindrical; circularity; sphericity; cylindrical form; rotundity; as
   the roundness of the globe, of the orb of the sun, of a ball, of a
   bowl, &c.

   2. Fullness; smoothness of flow; as the roundness of a period.

   3. Openness; plainness; boldness; positiveness; as the roundness of an
   assertion.
